  "story_title": "The Architecture of Scale",
  "story_text": "Throughout my career, I've believed that great software architecture is invisible. It doesn't scream for attention; it silently supports millions of concurrent transactions without breaking a sweat. My journey started in high-frequency trading, where every microsecond counted, and evolved into leading platform engineering for global SaaS platforms.",
  "anecdote_title": "A Midnight Crisis Solved",
  "anecdote_text": "During a critical Black Friday launch, a major database locking issue threatened to take down our checkout system. Instead of applying a temporary band-aid, I quickly orchestrated a distributed cache bypass that reduced database load by 80% in under fifteen minutes, saving the company millions in potential lost revenue."
